---
import SectionHeading from "@/components/SectionHeading.astro"
import TerminalWindow from "@/components/TerminalWindow.astro"
import MediaPlaceholder from "@/components/MediaPlaceholder.astro"
---

<section id="cli" class="border-b">
	<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 sm:py-24">
		<div class="grid items-start gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16">
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
				<SectionHeading eyebrow="cli" title="Scriptable down to the last pane.">
					<p>
						The launcher is optional. Every capability is a plain subcommand you can call from
						any shell, pipe into scripts, or hand to CI — with tab completion for PowerShell,
						bash and zsh.
					</p>
				</SectionHeading>
				<MediaPlaceholder
					kind="image"
					aspect="aspect-video"
					label="Screenshot: the ordo launcher TUI — purple sidebar listing saved sessions, live agent log on the right, single-key command bar at the bottom."
				/>
			</div>
			<TerminalWindow title="pwsh · ordo help">
				<pre class="whitespace-pre"><span class="text-primary">PS&gt;</span> ordo help
<span class="font-bold">ordo</span> — a terminal multiplexer for orchestrating AI agents

<span class="text-muted-foreground">Session commands:</span>
  ordo                 open the launcher in a fresh window
  ordo new             start a fresh session immediately
  ordo restore &lt;id&gt;    reopen a saved session
  ordo sessions        list saved sessions
  ordo delete &lt;id&gt;     delete a saved session

<span class="text-muted-foreground">Agent commands:</span>
  ordo agents          list live agent panes
  ordo spawn           spawn an agent pane
  ordo send &lt;pane&gt;     send a message to a pane
  ordo read &lt;pane&gt;     read a pane's output
  ordo broadcast       send a message to every agent
  ordo status          show agent statuses
  ordo interrupt &lt;pane&gt;  interrupt a pane</pre>
			</TerminalWindow>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
